
## Description  
This project is a text-based Python quiz that helps users discover their MBTI 16-personality type by answering 30 simple Yes/No questions.  
Users can navigate forward through questions or go back to change their previous answers, making the quiz flexible and user-friendly.  

The quiz tallies answers for each personality trait and calculates the final MBTI type with a brief description.

## Languages and Utilities Used  
- Python 3  
- Built-in input/output functions  
- Dictionary for trait scoring and mapping opposites  

## Environments Used  
- VS Code / Local Python Terminal / Any Python 3 compatible environment  

## Installation  
1. Ensure you have Python 3 installed on your system. You can download it from [python.org](https://www.python.org/downloads/).  
2. Download or clone this repository to your local machine.  
3. Navigate to the project folder in your terminal or command prompt.

## Usage  
1. Run the Python script with the command:  
   ```bash
   python pymbti_quiz.py
